         <abstract id="aspace_dc5d9dceeb1880726f76e52c0901b46c">The collection includes 88 black and white lantern slides on topics related to public health used for lectures at the Yale School of Medicine, Department of Public Health. Part or all of the collection was created and/or used by C.-E. A. (Charles-Edward Amory) Winslow, the founder of the department. Slide content includes photographs, illustrations, text, and charts. Some of the slides were made by Excelsior Illustrating Company, 219 Sixth Avenue, New York City.</abstract>
